messages.content: What is the purpose of ComfyUI-Pymunk?
ComfyUI-Pymunk is a custom node or plugin that extends the functionality of ComfyUI, a GUI that uses stable diffusion models to generate images and videos.
Where can the basic workflow example for ComfyUI-Pymunk be found?
The basic workflow example for ComfyUI-Pymunk can be found in the provided GitHub repository link: https://github.com/chaojie/ComfyUI-Pymunk/blob/main/workflow.json
What file contains the basic workflow example in the ComfyUI-Pymunk GitHub repository?
The basic workflow example for ComfyUI-Pymunk is contained in the 'workflow.json' file in the GitHub repository.
Is there a visual representation of the basic workflow example for ComfyUI-Pymunk?
Yes, there is a visual representation of the basic workflow example for ComfyUI-Pymunk. It is an image file named 'wf_basic.png'.
What is the file format of the visual representation of the basic workflow example in ComfyUI-Pymunk?
The file format of the visual representation of the basic workflow example in ComfyUI-Pymunk is PNG (Portable Network Graphics).
Is there a video example demonstrating the usage of ComfyUI-Pymunk?
Yes, there is a video example demonstrating the usage of ComfyUI-Pymunk. It is a GIF file named 'video.gif'.
What is the file format of the video example demonstrating the usage of ComfyUI-Pymunk?
The file format of the video example demonstrating the usage of ComfyUI-Pymunk is GIF (Graphics Interchange Format).
